  "narrative": {
    "intro": "The federal engineering services market for NAICS 541330 recorded $30.1B in obligations in FY2026 to date. Obligations were down 41.8% year over year, with 17,003 awards made and an average award size of $1.8M. Fiscal-year comparisons show a peak in recent years at $52.5B in FY24 and $51.7B in FY25, followed by the current FY26 total of $30.1B. The Department of Defense accounted for the largest share of FY2026 to date obligations at $22.8B, with the General Services Administration next at $3.3B. A small set of prime contractors captured substantial FY2026 to date obligations: ELECTRIC BOAT CORPORATION received $6.8B, while BOOZ ALLEN HAMILTON INC and SCIENCE APPLICATIONS INTERNATIONAL CORPORATION received $955M and $849M respectively. The data reflect fiscal activity to date rather than full-year totals, and they show concentration of dollars in defense and a handful of large primes alongside thousands of smaller awards.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How did FY2026 to date compare with prior fiscal years?",
        "body": "Obligations in FY2026 to date were $30.1B, lower than each of the last five fiscal years. Obligations were down 41.8% year over year compared with the prior fiscal year total of $51.7B in FY25. Recent fiscal-year peaks included $52.5B in FY24 and $47.8B in FY23."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors dominate obligations in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense led buying with $22.8B in obligations, followed by the General Services Administration with $3.3B. ELECTRIC BOAT CORPORATION was the top vendor with $6.8B, and BOOZ ALLEN HAMILTON INC and SCIENCE APPLICATIONS INTERNATIONAL CORPORATION followed with $955M and $849M respectively."
      }
    ]
